title: Investigation of the reaction Al-27(p,a0)Mg-24 in the proton energy range 1-2.5 MeV.

x4freetext: Investigation of the reaction Al-27(p,a0)Mg-24 in the
proton energy range 1-2.5 MeV.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Izv. Rossiiskoi Akademii Nauk, Ser.Fiz., Vol.28, p.46 (1964)
Jour: Bull.Russian Academy of Sciences - Physics, Vol.28, p.47 (1965)

x4freetext: The energy spread in the incident beam was 0.25%.
The reaction products were recorded by two
semiconductor detectors of the type ORTEC-100A-40. One
of them with solid angle 2.1*10**(-3) sr, was placed at
the angle 135 degr. with respect to the beam and used
as a monitor. The other detector could be rotated
around the target without disturbing the vacuum in the
range of scattering angles 30-150 degr. in the
laboratory system. The solid angle of the rotating
counter was 1.9*10**(-3) sr.
Self-supporting targets 27Al of 20-50 mu-g/cm2
thickness were prepared by evaporation in vacuum.
Data digitizing error
REFERENCE code was corrected.
